## Project Overview
- This is a Node.js CLI tool for automated code review
- Uses CommonJS modules (require/module.exports)
- Target runtime: Node.js 18+
- Coding style: Follow standard.js conventions, 2-space indent

## Architecture
- src/cli.js - CLI entry point (commander.js)
- src/reviewer.js - Core review logic, builds prompts, calls AI
- src/github.js - GitHub API integration (PR diff fetch, comments)
- src/config.js - Configuration loader (.coderevrc.json)
- src/cache.js - Review result cache with SHA256 diff hashing
- src/rules.js - Rule engine with predefined + custom rules

## Conventions
- Error messages: Use chalk for colored output, always prefix with ✖/⚠/✔
- Async: Prefer async/await over raw promises
- API keys: Never hardcode, always read from config or env vars
- Testing: Use node:test, all exports should have test coverage
